;re being willfuly obtuse.</p></div><div class="reply"></div></div></li></ol></li><li class="pingback even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-7758873" data-sort-time="1555508138"><div id="div-comment-7758873" class="comment-body"><div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><div class="comment-author vcard"> <cite class="fn"><strong><a href='http://ifttt.itbehere.com/2019/04/17/barr-kicks-off-the-next-big-fight-over-immigration-reason-roundup/' rel='external nofollow ugc' class='url'>Barr Kicks Off the Next Big Fight Over Immigration: Reason Roundup &#8211; iftttwall</a></strong></cite></div> <a href="https://reason.com/2019/04/16/so-much-for-the-anti-war-president/#comment-7758873">April.17.2019 at 9:35 am </a></div><div class="comment-content"><p>[&#8230;] in Yemen. &#8220;Since taking office, Trump&#8217;s track record has been decidedly mixed,&#8221;notes Reason&#8216;sEric [&#8230;]</p></div><div class="reply"></div></div></li><li class="comment byuser odd alt thread-even depth-1 parent " id="comment-7758888" data-sort-time="1555508463"><div id="div-comment-7758888" class="comment-body"><div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><div class="comment-author vcard"> <cite class="fn"><strong>Moderation4ever</strong></cite></div> <a href="https://reason.com/2019/04/16/so-much-for-the-anti-war-president/#comment-7758888">April.17.2019 at 9:41 am </a></div><div class="comment-content"><p>I cannot understand the desire to get into a war with Iran, either directly or by proxy. The war with Iraq has been nothing but a quagmire. We won the war but lost the peace. We are mired down in Afghanistan. Adding war with Iran will just make things worse. It is time that we get serious about peace in the middle east and that should start with these proxy wars.</p></div><div class="reply"></div></div><ol class="children"><li class="comment byuser even depth-2 parent " id="comment-7759567" data-sort-time="1555535895"><div id="div-comment-7759567" class="comment-body"><div class="